parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause erratic electrical problems, including malfunctioning of signal lights, blinkers, windshield wipers, and power windows, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ignition switch sticks in the on position
electrical accessories such as brake lights
power windows get stuck in the down position
sudden loss of electrical power with no prior warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical system failures, leading to malfunctioning of critical systems such as turn signals, lights, and horn, which can increase the risk of accidents. Additionally, the inability to turn the vehicle off can lead to safety risks.
symptoms: intermittent malfunctioning of turn signals and headlights
ignition switch stuck or unable to move
inability to turn the vehicle off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Catalytic Converter Failure on Manual Transmission Audis
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to stall or experience poor engine performance, leading to potential safety risks and increased emissions.
symptoms: the engine runs rough or misfires
the vehicle experiences poor fuel economy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misadjustment of the cam sprocket/timing can cause the vehicle to stall, especially at traffic lights, leading to potential safety risks and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls at traffic lights or when idling
the vehicle experiences poor engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Pulls to the Right due to Misalignment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's tendency to pull to the right can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, and make it difficult to steer, which can lead to driver fatigue and decreased safety.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to the right
